<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5> feel the pulse of something • have a feel on the pulse of something</xh5><p> <i>feel the pulse of something</i>—(also: keep one’s finger on the pulse of something ) keep track of the current developments and trends in smth.: What consummate skill must be his who thus <u>feels the pulse of</u> fashion, recognizing in its beat the indications of this or that tendency...</p><p> <i>have a feel on the pulse of something—</i>have sensitivity for and understanding of smth.: In day to day dealing with cross-sections of society, they tend to <u>have a feel on the pulse of</u> society: its ills, travails and aspirations.</p> </entry>
